lead_paragraph: That’s what George Washington said. Imagine a modern presidential candidate saying that.

headline.print_headline: Don’t Vote for Me, I’m Not Worthy
headline.main: Don’t Vote for Me, I’m Not Worthy

snippet: That’s what George Washington said. Imagine a modern presidential candidate saying that....
abstract: Op-Ed article by historian Julie Miller reflects on journals and letters of George Washington, and how they reveal man who struggled with very idea of becoming president; posits future generations will likely see current presidential candidates as figures created by unique conditions of current historical moment, much as people today view Washington.
